content.description: Sart as low as you can on the Arete and go up.  Great topout and super fun.
content.protection: Couple of pads and a spotter
content.location:

climbs.name: Karen's Stuck at Home with the Kids

content.description: Start at lowest matching hold and head up to high large hold.  Very balancy and sequency.
content.location: From western parking lot head east on main trail.  One you past the last large boulder in clear cut head up about 100 meters. On a large boulder about 15 feet high and faces to the east.

content.description: Sitdown start at lowest left hand side of the crack.  Head up and to the right.  DO NOT USE the big offset block for feet or hands.  Follow crack the whole way up.
content.location: From western parking lot head east on main trail.  At the last big boulder in the clear cut head up about 100 meters.  On boulder just east of "Karen's Stuck home with the Kids" problem.
